text: Kathy Poohachof is a retired American para-alpine skier. She competed for the United States at the 1980 Winter Paralympics in Geilo, Norway, and the 1984 Winter Paralympics in Innsbruck, Austria. Overall, she won five silver medals in alpine skiing. == References == == Other websites == * Kathy Poohachof at Paralympic.org Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Alpine skiers at the 1984 Winter Paralympics Category:Medalists at the 1984 Winter Paralympics Category:Paralympic silver medalists for the United States
